<div id="review_1942285928" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1942285928" />
    <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro"><img alt="Michael Finocchiaro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576692048p2/48483884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1942285928?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Finocchiaro" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro">Michael Finocchiaro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=american-21st-c">american-21st-c</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1942285928" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3253692352879536109">I discovered Rachel Maddow a little late because I live in France and I only learned about her on MSNBC with her stories that I follow about Drumpf&amp;Co. Her book Drift about the change in US military policy is well-researched provides a lot of insight into how America modified executive power in declaring war from being necessarily approved by Congress to war by proxy using mercenaries. It does have a political event but as the cover says ultimately the logic underneath her argument is not partis</span>
  <span id="freeText3253692352879536109" style="display:none">I discovered Rachel Maddow a little late because I live in France and I only learned about her on MSNBC with her stories that I follow about Drumpf&amp;Co. Her book Drift about the change in US military policy is well-researched provides a lot of insight into how America modified executive power in declaring war from being necessarily approved by Congress to war by proxy using mercenaries. It does have a political event but as the cover says ultimately the logic underneath her argument is not partisan. Her writing displays lot of wit and is very readable. I had already forgotten about US intervention in Granada as well as Reagan's Iran-Contra scandal and Rachel explains these both (as well as Gulf War I&amp;II, the Balkans the long-running occupation in the Middle East) in the overwhelming context of the drifting of decision making power for armed conflict into the hands of the President bypassing Congress and the Abrams act. Unfortunately, the trend did not improve under the last two Democratic Presidents, in fact it got worse. And worse yet, Drumpf's flag-waving and random use of weapons is even more terrifying. She also talks about the problems and dangers of maintaining the massive nuclear arsenal - something I have not yet heard about from Drumpf, Inc yet. <br />She does conclude with a list of things that can be done - again mostly bi-partisan, no-nonsense propositions. I would recommend this book for those who wish to understand how the armed forces have evolved and to see the scale of the problems this poses.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3253692352879536109" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


