    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_617727859" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/617727859" />
    <a title="Debbie &quot;DJ&quot;" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12620745-debbie-dj"><img alt="Debbie &quot;DJ&quot;" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1407426768p2/12620745.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/617727859?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debbie &quot;DJ&quot;" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debbie &quot;DJ&quot;" href="/user/show/12620745-debbie-dj">Debbie &quot;DJ&quot;</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12620745-debbie-dj?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12620745-debbie-dj?shelf=political">political</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer617727859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17761932048252240688"><br/> <br/> This book is an extremely important look at America and our war policy. While such a topic may seem dry, Maddow&apos;s book took me on a journey that was captivating. Have you ever wondered why we seem so disconnected from our current wars, why our economy is broke, or what has become of our over 5000 nuclear warheads? Our founding fathers created what is known as the &quot;Addams Doctrine&quot;, which places the power to go to war in the hands of congress. This was done to insure no one person could decide </span>
  <span id="freeText17761932048252240688" style="display:none"><br /> <br /> This book is an extremely important look at America and our war policy. While such a topic may seem dry, Maddow's book took me on a journey that was captivating. Have you ever wondered why we seem so disconnected from our current wars, why our economy is broke, or what has become of our over 5000 nuclear warheads? Our founding fathers created what is known as the "Addams Doctrine", which places the power to go to war in the hands of congress. This was done to insure no one person could decide to take us to war. This book chronicles our drift away from that policy. <br /><br />The most profound drift occurred with the startling lies of president Reagan. The precedence he set has been followed and expanded ever since. No longer can I sit on my sofa and hear the president "informed congress" of his drone strikes. Mainstream journalism does not inform us of the atrocities our government commits. While our current situation is dire, Maddow leaves us with important ideas to get us out of our current situation, and thus hope. If every American read this book our world just might have the courage to change. Buy the way, we've only LOST 5 or 6 nuclear bombs!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17761932048252240688" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

